A guy, who is around twenty or twenty-one years old. ends up a phishing victim. He gets a call from a company, who says that they are a company who will protect his identy for free, as long as he gives his personal information. He happily gives his information, saying that he doesn't want to get his identity stolen. "well sir, we are just trying to make the world a better place, without the people who steal the identities." the lady over the phone tell him with a smirk. A few days later, he gets a call from his bank telling him that he is over his cost limit for the month, and wants to know if he is the one responsible for it. He responds with shock "NO!" He calls back the number that said they would keep his identity safe, and they didn' awnser. 
